- cs.IT (Information Theory) is relevant as the paper discusses the complexity of median filtering and its relationship to sorting. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as median filtering is a common preprocessing step in machine learning applications. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is also relevant as median filtering is commonly used in multimedia applications such as audio and video processing.
